\ Pairs, equality: = is raw structural comparison (head then tail), no deref.
\ Distinct pair objects with the same structure compare equal; logic vars in a
\ pair compare by identity, not by their (un)bound value.

\ structurally equal lists, distinct objects, compare equal
[( 1 2 3 null )] [( 1 2 3 null )] = . cr            \ 1
\ one differing element
[( 1 2 3 null )] [( 1 2 4 null )] = . cr            \ 0
\ a proper prefix is not equal (shorter tail)
[( 1 2 null )] [( 1 2 3 null )] = . cr              \ 0
\ a pair equals itself
[( 5 6 7 null )] dup = . cr                         \ 1
\ dotted pairs (non-nil tail) compare structurally
3 4 cons  3 4 cons  = . cr                          \ 1
3 4 cons  3 5 cons  = . cr                          \ 0
\ nested structure
[( [( 1 null )] [( 2 null )] null )] [( [( 1 null )] [( 2 null )] null )] = . cr   \ 1
[( [( 1 null )] [( 2 null )] null )] [( [( 1 null )] [( 9 null )] null )] = . cr   \ 0
\ different tags are not equal
[( 1 null )] 5 = . cr                               \ 0
[( 1 2 3 null )] [ 1 2 3 ] = . cr                   \ 0
\ logic vars in a pair compare by identity
variable X   lvar to X
variable Y   lvar to Y
[( 1 X null )] [( 1 X null )] = . cr                \ 1   same var
[( 1 X null )] [( 1 Y null )] = . cr                \ 0   different vars
\ lexicographic ordering via lt / gt
[( 1 2 null )] [( 1 3 null )] lt . cr               \ 1
[( 1 3 null )] [( 1 2 null )] gt . cr               \ 1

bye
